        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 8:35PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 835 PM MDT/935 PM CDT/, the public reported a strong thunderstorm
11 miles south of Sharon Springs, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of Wichita,
southeastern Wallace, southwestern Logan and northeastern Greeley
Counties, including the following locations... Marienthal and
Selkirk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT/1100
PM CDT/ for west central Kansas.</instruction>
